item.title: StarStruck Full Part 2/8 HQ
item.description:
StarStruck Full Part 2/8 HQ
StarStruck Full Part 2/8 HQ The Movie begins with Teen pop sensation, Christopher Wilde (Sterling Knight), performing on stage with his hit song Starstruck. Back in Michigan, Jessica Olsen (Danielle Campbell) is her Christopher Wilde fanatic sister Sara Olsen (Maggie Castle) comes back from the groceries with their parents. The television reports of Christopher Wilde picking up six music awards and getting a TWOx platinum for his new album "Real Wilde". After the report on Wilde, Sara comments on how great Wilde is. Jessica finds Sara ridiculously unrealistic when she herself do not even know Christopher Wilde in person. Jessica bets that Wilde is not that great a person as he seems on TV. Sara argues back with her knowledge about Christopher Wilde; for example, where Wilde eats, works, shops, surfs and parties. Christopher is shown with his best pal, Stubby (Brandon Mychal Smith, at the below 21 club who meet Wilde's girlfriend, Alexis Bender (Chelsea Staub). Alexis with Wilde of her birthday which Wilde completely forgets and which he promises to sing. Wilde quickly reassures her that he will be there for her birthday. Alexis then questions of something being amiss. Stubby is irritated by Alexis's presence and is even more irritated when Alexis blogged about Wilde's whereabouts and attracted the paparazzi. Alexis, with her obsession with attention, poses for the paparazzi while Wilde tries to get rid of them. Back in Michigan, Jessica and Sara attend McKinley High School where they had a dispute over the invitation of the school's dance. Sara insults Jessica as Jessica doesn't know how to dance. In school, Sara's best friend AJ, asks of whether Sara is going to be bringing her camera to California so as to take more photos Wilde's life. Jessica questions about their obsession with Wilde. AJ finds Jessica super insulting when she mentions Wilde as "THIS GUY". Sara mentions that Jessica can play shuffle boards with Grandma while she's going to meet Christopher Wilde. Jessica questions on how are they going to be able to meet Wilde. AJ mapped out Wilde's action for the past 18 months and that is shown in a Christopher Wilde picture book. At Wilde's house, both his parents is revealed to be working for Wilde as his personal manager. Wilde's parents are very anxious as a famous movie director, Alan Smith, is coming down to offer him an opportunity to star in a movie. Alan Smith notes that Wilde is a talent and offers him this opportunity to star in a movie. However, Smith's partners are not convinced as what they see is a spoil punk who likes to tangle with the paparazzi. Alan requests of Wilde to prove that he is serious about the movie and a committed actor. Smith asks of Wilde to stay home and out of the press for the next few days. Upon arriving at California, Sara is devastated by a notice that those under the age of 25 cannot drive or rent a car from the car rentals even with a license. This devastates Sara but was relieved upon hearing that their Grandmother has a car for her to borrow. Barbara Olson (Beth Littleford) was shocked but pleased to see her mother with her new found love. Jessica hugged her grandmother and her grandma asks Sara to take an old antique pink car for a spin. Sara did not want to be embarrassed being seen driving in this outdated car. Jessica suggests that she could come play Shuffle boards with Grandma if she likes.
